This subject gives an overview of the theoretical basis of health promotion; of principles of health promotion in different target groups and on different levels; of the fields of mental health, health and risk behaviours, of the theoretical basis and possibilities for implementation of health promotion interventions. Medical students get knowledge on health promotion activities and main current health problems in Estonia. The framework of this subject is based on possible arising health problems in daily work of physicians.Objectives/eesmärkid:  - to give basic knowledge in general terms, principles and conceptions of health promotion; - to give an overview of  the Estonian National Health Plan and to describe the place of health promotion in health system; -  to give an overview of mental health, health and risk behaviours, and possibilities of health promotion in different target groups; - to give a knowledge in theoretical basis of health promotion interventions and to introduce possibilities for implementation on different levels;Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - is familiar with main principles of health promotion; - has an overview of the Estonian National Health Plan; - knows main fields of health and risk behaviours and is able to interpret research results of different fields; - knows possibilities of health promotion interventions in different target groups and on different levels and is able to use theoretical knowledge in preparation of intervention programs;
